  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7, then take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Chop your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into fries and add them to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>and mix to combine, then put the tray[s] in the oven for 20-25 min or until golden and crisp</p><p>Cut the <strong>pepper[s]</strong> in half (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon)</p>",
      "order": 1,
